{"WATCH":[{"def":"The act of watching; forbearance of sleep; vigil; wakeful, vigilant, or constantly observant attention; close observation; guard; preservative or preventive vigilance; formerly, a watching or guarding by night.","pos":""},{"def":"One who watches, or those who watch; a watchman, or a body of watchmen; a sentry; a guard.","pos":""}],"WATCH MEETING":[{"def":"A religious meeting held in the closing hours of the year.","pos":""}],"WATCHDOG":[{"def":"A dog kept to watch and guard premises or property, and to give notice of the approach of intruders.","pos":""}],"WATCHER":[{"def":"One who watches; one who sits up or continues; a diligent observer; specifically, one who attends upon the sick during the night.","pos":""}],"WATCHES":[{"def":"The leaves of Sarace.","pos":""}],"WATCHET":[{"def":"Pale or light blue.","pos":""}],"WATCHFUL":[{"def":"Full of watch; vigilant; attentive; careful to observe closely; observant; cautious; -- with of before the thing to be regulated or guarded; as, to be watchful of one's behavior; and with against before the thing to be avoided; as, to be watchful against the growth of vicious habits.","pos":""}],"WATCHHOUSE":[{"def":"A house in which a watch or guard is placed.","pos":""},{"def":"A place where persons under temporary arrest by the police of a city are kept; a police station; a lockup.","pos":""}],"WATCHMAKER":[{"def":"One whose occupation is to make and repair watches.","pos":""}],"WATCHMAN":[{"def":"One set to watch; a person who keeps guard; a guard; a sentinel.","pos":""},{"def":"Specifically, one who guards a building, or the streets of a city, by night.","pos":""}],"WATCHTOWER":[{"def":"A tower in which a sentinel is placed to watch for enemies, the approach of danger, or the like.","pos":""}],"WATCHWORD":[{"def":"A word given to sentinels, and to such as have occasion to visit the guards, used as a signal by which a friend is known from an enemy, or a person who has a right to pass the watch from one who has not; a countersign; a password.","pos":""},{"def":"A sentiment or motto; esp.","pos":""}]}